Package org.lightsleep.entity

Annotation classes and interfaces you use when creating entity classes.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Composite Deprecated
    As of release 3.2.0, instead use PostSelect, PreInsert, PostUpdate and PostDelete interfaces
    PostDelete
    If an entity class implements this interface, delete(E) and delete(Iterable) method of Sql<E> class invoke postDelete method of the entity class after executing DELETE SQL.
    PostInsert
    If an entity class implements this interface, insert(E) and insert(Iterable) method of Sql<E> class invoke postInsert method of the entity class after executing INSERT SQL.
    PostLoad Deprecated
    As of release 3.2.0, instead use PostSelect interface
    PostSelect
    If an entity class implements this interface, select methods of Sql<E> class invoke postSelect method of the entity class after each entity is retrieved by executing SELECT SQL.
    PostUpdate
    If an entity class implements this interface, update(E) and update(Iterable) methods of Sql<E> class invoke postUpdate method of the entity class after executing UPDATE SQL.
    PreDelete
    If an entity class implements this interface, delete(E) and delete(Iterable) methods of Sql<E> class invoke preDelete method of the entity class before executing DELETE SQL.
    PreInsert
    If an entity class implements this interface, insert(E) and insert(Iterable) methods of Sql<E> class invoke preInsert method of the entity class before executing INSERT SQL.
    PreStore Deprecated
    As of release 3.2.0, instead use both PreInsert and PreUpdate interfaces
    PreUpdate
    If an entity class implements this interface, update(E) and update(Iterable) methods of Sql<E> class invoke preUpdate method of the entity class before executing UPDATE SQL.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Column
    Indicates the name of column related to the field.
    ColumnProperties
    Indicates an array of ColumnProperty annotations.
    ColumnProperty
    Indicates the column name related to the field defined in superclass.
    ColumnType
    Indicates the type of column related to the field.
    ColumnTypeProperties
    Indicates an array of ColumnTypeProperty annotations.
    ColumnTypeProperty
    Indicates the column type related to the field defined in superclass.
    Insert
    Indicates an expression instead of the field value used in INSERT SQL.
    InsertProperties
    Indicates an array of InsertProperty annotations.
    InsertProperty
    Indicates an expression instead of the value of the field defined in superclass used in INSERT SQL.
    Key
    Indicates that the column related to the field is part of the primary key.
    KeyProperties
    Indicates an array of KeyProperty annotations.
    KeyProperty
    Indicates that the column related to the field is part of the primary key.
    NonColumn
    Indicates that the field not related to any column.
    NonColumnProperties
    Indicates an array of NonColumnProperty annotations.
    NonColumnProperty
    Indicates that the field defined in superclass is not related to any column.
    NonInsert
    Indicates that the column related the field is not used in INSERT SQL.
    NonInsertProperties
    Indicates an array of NonInsertProperty annotations.
    NonInsertProperty
    Indicates that the column related the field defined in superclass is not used in INSERT SQL.
    NonSelect
    Indicates that the column related the field is not used in SELECT SQL.
    NonSelectProperties
    Indicates an array of NonSelectProperty annotations.
    NonSelectProperty
    Indicates that the column related the field defined in superclass is not used in SELECT SQL.
    NonUpdate
    Indicates that the column related the field is not used in UPDATE SQL.
    NonUpdateProperties
    Indicates an array of NonUpdateProperty annotations.
    NonUpdateProperty
    Indicates that the column related the field defined in superclass is not used in UPDATE SQL.
    Select
    Indicates ta column expression instead of the column name in SELECT SQL.
    SelectProperties
    Indicates an array of SelectProperty annotations.
    SelectProperty
    Indicates an expression instead of the name of the column related to the field defined in superclass used in SELECT SQL.
    Table
    Indicates the table name related to the class.
    Update
    Indicates an expression instead of the field value used in UPDATE SQL.
    UpdateProperties
    Indicates an array of UpdateProperty annotations.
    UpdateProperty
    Indicates an expression instead of the value of the field defined in superclass used in UPDATE SQL.
